# No manual cluster interventions (GitOps)

## Agent mandate

Before any `kubectl` that **writes** to `homie-staging` / `homie-production` /
`argocd` Applications‚Äô managed resources, stop and follow this rule.

**Desired state changes go to git first.** Argo CD Sync applies them.
Manual live edits are a defect, not a shortcut.

If you catch yourself about to ‚Äújust set the image / apply the Job / edit the
Deploy so we can continue‚Äù ‚Äî **do not**. That is the failure mode that causes
reconciler fights and configuration drift.

## Forbidden (staging / production)

Do **not** run these against Argo-managed workloads (apps under
`homie-workloads` / `homie-workloads-production`, migrate hooks, worker, etc.):

| Forbidden | Why |
|-----------|-----|
| `kubectl set image` | Bypasses git pin; Argo reverts or drifts |
| `kubectl edit` / `kubectl patch` on Deployments, Services, ConfigMaps, Jobs owned by Argo | Live ‚â† git |
| `kubectl apply -f` / `apply -k` of `infra/k3s/overlays/{staging,production}` | Bypasses Argo; creates last-applied drift |
| `kubectl apply` of one-off migrate Jobs/ConfigMaps ‚Äúto unblock‚Äù | Leaves OutOfSync; migrate belongs in git PreSync |
| `kubectl delete` of Argo-managed resources to ‚Äúforce recreate‚Äù (except documented break-glass) | Masks Sync bugs |
| Deleting `argocd-repo-server` / routine `Replace=true` Sync to make a pin stick | Treats symptoms; fix git render + Sync |
| Changing container env/args/replicas on a live Pod/Deploy for a ‚Äúquick test‚Äù | Use git + Sync or local overlay |

## Allowed without a git commit

| Allowed | Scope |
|---------|--------|
| `kubectl get/describe/logs/top` | Read-only |
| `kubectl exec` into Temporal (or documented trigger) to **start/signal workflows** | Runtime control, not desired-state |
| `kubectl -n argo create -f` from **committed** `examples/*.yaml` / WorkflowTemplates already applied from git | Submit work; spec still in repo |
| `kubectl -n argo apply -f templates/‚Ä¶` | **Only until** templates are themselves an Argo app ‚Äî prefer committing template changes first; do not use this for app Deployments |
| Out-of-band Secrets via `scripts/apply-homie-*-secret.sh` | Documented exception; values never in git |
| Argo: `annotate ‚Ä¶ refresh`, `patch` Application **operation.sync** | Reconcile to git ‚Äî not change desired state |
| Local lane (`homie` / `overlays/local`) | Dev; still prefer commit when sharing |

## Required path for common goals

### Ship new worker code / Slack fixes / scrape changes

1. Commit + push to `staging` (or `main` for prod).
2. Submit **committed** `homie-build-images` (or wait for build poll when wired).
3. Commit `chore(k3s): pin ‚Ä¶ newTag: staging-<sha>` in
   `infra/k3s/overlays/<lane>/kustomization.yaml`.
4. Push ‚Üí Argo hard-refresh ‚Üí Sync.
5. **Verify:** live Deployment image == git `images[].newTag` **and**
   Application `sync=Synced`.  
   Sync `phase=Succeeded` alone is **not** enough.

**Never** bridge a stuck pin with `kubectl set image`.

### Schema / migrate

1. Put SQL + Job/ConfigMap changes in git (`drizzle/`, `scrape-db-migrate`, overlay env).
2. Push ‚Üí Argo Sync (PreSync migrate runs from the **lane branch**).
3. Do not `kubectl apply` a one-off migrate Job as the lasting fix.

### Env / config

Follow `iac-env-config.mdc`: edit ConfigMap/overlay in git ‚Üí Sync.  
Do not `kubectl set env` / edit live ConfigMaps for Argo-managed apps.

## Decision tree (agents)

```text
Need cluster behavior to change?
  ‚îú‚îÄ Is it only secrets/values? ‚Üí apply-*-secret.sh (out of band)
  ‚îú‚îÄ Is it start/signal a workflow? ‚Üí exec/Temporal trigger (no manifest edit)
  ‚îú‚îÄ Is it desired state (image, replicas, env, Job, probe, ‚Ä¶)?
  ‚îÇ     ‚Üí edit git ‚Üí push ‚Üí Argo Sync ‚Üí verify live == git
  ‚îî‚îÄ ‚ÄúBut Sync is stuck / wrong tag‚Äù?
        ‚Üí diagnose git tip vs Application revision vs rendered kustomize
        ‚Üí fix git or Argo source/cache
        ‚Üí NOT kubectl patch/set image
```

## Break-glass (rare)

Label the action **break-glass** in the reply to the user. Then:

1. Smallest possible write; prefer Secrets-only or read-only.
2. Same change (or revert) committed to git within the same working session when possible.
3. Argo Sync until `Synced` and live matches git; remove leftover imperative objects.

If the user asks you to `set image` or `apply -k` staging to ‚Äúsave time,‚Äù refuse the bypass, explain drift, and offer the git ‚Üí pin ‚Üí Sync path instead.

